    <h2 dir="auto" data-sourcepos="19:1-19:23">
      <a aria-hidden="true" href="#running-the-calendar" class="anchor" id="user-content-running-the-calendar"></a>Running the Calendar</h2>
    <p dir="auto" data-sourcepos="20:1-20:195">To run the Calendar, you need to have <em>docker</em> and <em>docker compose plugin</em> installed in your machine. After cloning the repository, go to the project root directory and run the following command:</p>
    <p dir="auto" data-sourcepos="22:1-22:34"><code>docker compose --profile prod up</code></p>
    <p dir="auto" data-sourcepos="24:1-24:69">You can access the calendar through the address: <a rel="nofollow noreferrer noopener" href="http://0.0.0.0:3000/">http://0.0.0.0:3000/</a></p>
    </p>
    <h2 dir="auto" data-sourcepos="26:1-26:20">
      <a aria-hidden="true" href="#running-the-tests" class="anchor" id="user-content-running-the-tests"></a>Running the tests</h2>
    <p dir="auto" data-sourcepos="27:1-27:56">To run the tests, you can execute the following command:</p>
    <p dir="auto" data-sourcepos="29:1-29:64"><code>docker compose --profile test run --rm web-test bin/rails test</code></p>
    <h2 dir="auto" data-sourcepos="31:1-31:23">
      <a aria-hidden="true" href="#running-system-tests" class="anchor" id="user-content-running-system-tests"></a>Running System Tests</h2>
    <p dir="auto" data-sourcepos="32:1-32:72">Finally, to run the System Tests, you can execute the following command:</p>
    <p dir="auto" data-sourcepos="34:1-34:71"><code>docker compose --profile test run --rm web-test bin/rails test:system</code></p>
    <p dir="auto" data-sourcepos="36:1-37:23">You can view the System Tests execution in your browser, through this link: <a rel="nofollow noreferrer noopener" href="http://localhost:7900/">http://localhost:7900/</a>.
      First, click in Connect</p>
    <p dir="auto" style="text-align: center;">
      <img class="js-lazy-loaded qa-js-lazy-loaded" decoding="async" width="100%" src="<%= asset_path('noVNC.jpg') %>" loading="lazy">
    </p>
    <p dir="auto" data-sourcepos="43:1-43:75">Then, put <code>secret</code> in the Password field and click in <strong>Send Credentials</strong>.</p>
